# LifePilot Cursor rules

## Product scope (permanent)

LifePilot is a privacy-first daily-life assistant: tasks, reminders, personal/work events and schedules, unified Today timeline, morning/anytime briefing, conflict and preparation detection, weather/travel context, routines/preferences, explainable suggestions, and approval-gated external writes.

**Out of scope — remove, do not add:**
- Banking, balances, transactions, spending, budgets, bills, payments, investments
- Shopping, price tracking, checkout, purchase automation
- HealthKit / medical / health intelligence as a shipping MVP feature (deferred only)
- Apple Mail content ingestion and automatic message sending
- Embedding OpenAI or any API secrets in the client, repo, tests, or assets

## Architecture

`App → AppShell → Features → Core protocols/models ← Services/Integrations`  
`GhostBrain/Planning → Core only`

- Features depend on protocols, never concretions in Mocks/Services.
- AppShell is the composition root.
- AI never receives execution credentials and never calls system integrations directly.
- Every external write goes through ActionProposal → explicit Approval → Executor (revalidate, idempotent, auditable).

## Quality bar

- Offline-first with persisted LifePilot-owned data; Calendar/Reminders remain source of truth when connected.
- Least privilege; request permission only at the feature that needs it.
- Recommendations always carry evidence, freshness, and reason.
- No fake charts, dead buttons, or screenshot-as-implementation.
- Prefer extending existing DesignSystem / Core types over one-off styling or duplicate models.

## Workflow

- **Before any work:** `git fetch origin develop` and start from **latest `develop`**. Diff open PRs targeting `develop` and existing paths for the same issue/feature — **do not duplicate**. Prefer extending or superseding an open branch/PR over opening a parallel one.
- If another open PR already contains the change, update that branch (or clearly mark it superseded) instead of re-implementing.
- Work on `feature/*` or `cursor/*` branches — never commit directly to `main` or `develop`.
- Small conventional commits after verified slices.
- Update `docs/IMPLEMENTATION_STATUS.md` with real evidence after each stage.
- Never claim a check passed unless it ran and passed. If Xcode/swift is unavailable locally, say so and use CI results.
- Search the repo before creating replacements.
